rComments: Amazing professor, he is kind, helpful, go to his office hours and you will be ok, Physics is not easy and he understands that. Great course. Repeats much time so we understand properly.
unfortunately, his slides are very hard to read due to the color and organization, therefore it is hard to pay attention.

THE NICEST FIRST YEAR PROF EVER!!! seriously this professor is unlike any other in terms of how much he cares for his student. Go to him if you're struggling he will save you! Lectures are all theory and concepts (important for conceptual questions on test/exam) but tutorials are important for working out actual examples! Past tests are the key!

One of the best profs at UTM! He helps out greatly during office hours and always repeats important information in lectures. His lectures are very detailed and are more conceptual than practical so you must do homework questions or past midterms and tests that are posted to be able to do well in the course.

Seriously an amazing Prof. He truly cares and sympathizes with his students. TBH, I did not expect to do well in this course. He helped me out a lot. To prepare for midterm/exam, do plenty of past tests. Make sure to do error propagation for lab reports. Just keep up the material and make sure to understand the theories.

Good prof. Cares a lot about his students doing well and is passionate about teaching. Lectures are REALLY theory-heavy though, tutorials are basically the only problem-solving we got from instructors. Beware of lab reports. Tests are straightforward and questions are taken from past exams.

His lectures are very theory based, although it was mostly review from gr 11 physics. His lectures help visual learners. Hes a kind hearted prof who will try his very best to help you out. TA's are more tough then him. Go to class or skip class, just do problem sets and you're good. I hate physics but hes my fave prof. Give him a chance hes great.

This professor is the reason i have my degree now. He's a wonderful person, available, friendly and helpful. He's not the type that'll weed out the weak, he wants to give everyone a chance. If you try, even a little, you will definitely be rewarded.

Professor Ghobriel's exam and midterm was a joke. Completely based off of past tests and pretty straightforward aside from 1 or 2 questions. As long as your do plenty of practice work and study with a group that knows what they're doing as well, you'll be just fine. It's really important to not get overwhelmed with the tough lab reports though.
His course is boring but he is kind for everyone moreover if you study you will get idea grade

Lectures are pure theory. There's a sever lack of solving problems during lectures. Problems are mainly solved in tutorials, right before the quizzes. The lab reports are usually not directly related to what's going on in class. Prof is extremely willing to help students though. He does things like bell curve. The exams are predictable.

The lectures given by this professor are, to put it simple, awful. He essentially covers grade 11 material in a university course that states grade 12 physics as a prerequisite. However, the tests and labs, which are not led by him, go way beyond the material he teaches. His lectures are useless, and he speaks annoyingly slow and repeats too much.

Decent prof. Unless you never took any physics class in high school, lectures for the most part are fairly useless. DOWNLOAD ALL THE PAST EXAMS AND KNOW THE QUESTIONS, HE REPEATS ALOT!!! THEY SAVED MY SEMESTER!!
The lectures basically only taught the concepts, not how to do the problems. If you want to do well in this course, DO THE PROBLEM SET!
Test was way too hard

Good Prof! If you want to succeed in his class you'll need to practice calculation problems, and a lot of them. Know how to do questions that incorporate two or more types of theory. Don't focus on memorizing theory, focus on understanding how you can apply it. Overall pretty clear, nice guy. Pay attention and work hard and you'll do well :)

Course was only easy because of past tests/exams. Don't do the textbook questions!! The textbook questions are a joke and are only good for the quizzes. The midterm/exam questions are a lot harder. Suggest you buy a PHY package, he repeats a lot!

Great professor, but I will say that the course was only easy because of the past test/exams, if you can find someone to buy or get it from, it will make your life a lot easier in this course. The midterms/exams consisted of questions that weren't found in the book. Doing textbook work is useless to be honest.
Super enthusiastic!

This is one of the best profs I have met to this day. The way he explains the concepts with such enthusiasm is remarkable, it really helps you understand the concept quickly. A Side note one should always do the required textbook questions and previous exam questions. Although he may not repeat any questions the concepts remain the same.
im really scared about this course. i hope he doesn't fail me :(...i studied well n did problems but still i did very bad on the midterm and the exam

He is a very nice guy, wants everyone to succeed but students cant really get much out of hi lectures. He doesnt go over hard problems or problems of test level at all. He basically reads of the powerpoint and everything he says can be found in textbook. There is definitely lack of him solving things on board.
Please do examples on the board for easiness. Thank You.

He's a great teacher, despite the fact that he's teaching a very difficult course. Gives you all the knowledge you need to do well in the course, especially paired with his TA's. Goes through basic problems, if you want the harder questions, ask him and he'll gladly go through it. Very enthusiastic, I don't like physics, but I like this class.

A seemingly good professor, but also very midleading. Claimed the midterm would be fair and not to difficult yet most people failed and it was brutal. He taught well but only easy concepts, unneccessarily repeating the same easy material like what a force is many times without going into any difficult problems.

I went in with great expectations cuz I heard good stuff about this course but it was nothing like I expected. They changed stuff around this year, and the midterm was unnecessarily long & hard (avg was 43 AFTER a bell curve) and the prof taught nothing useful in lectures, just went over basic concepts..and then we were tested ridiculously. -5/10
The way he teaches is  interesting unlike other proff. Really encourages his students to strive for the best

Really amazing prof! He explains concepts really well and he's easy on the eyes. He's pretty entertaining with his visual aids. Read your notes and do book questions before lecture. His lecture discussions are directly from the slides so it's manageable to get an A in his class. The tests are a bit hard but as long as you studied, you'll do fine!!

Easy course to get an A in.. I was bad at physics in high school, but this course helped me gain by lost confidence back. Prof is very helpful in terms of extra help but dont expect to get a lot out of the lectures. Just do textbook problems and past midterms and tests and you will do great in this course! Cheers

Man oh man, I didn't take physics in high school but I went into this class reading the comments saying you can still do well.  Not entirely true cuz the fact of the matter is, he's a useless prof who doesn't tell you how to do examples in class (the point of physics).  He goes off on a million little tangents and his lectures have no substance C-

He's the only prof I know of that uses a trolly full of toys to explain concepts but it works! Labs may take a while to do so don't delay on them, they're easy to get a 80 on. Quizzes were far more difficult than tests and the TAs didn't explain much. His tests and exam aren't easy but they're easier than the TA's quizzes.

He is a really nice guy, unfortunately I fall asleep in his class, and I find his strong Italian accent extremely annoying.  If you took Grade 12 Physics and are in his 1st year class you won?t have to do much.  The quizzes are harder than his tests.

His tests are very hard, but he teaches well during class and is a nice guy. Make sure you go over EVERY example from his past tests, homework, and lectures since some of those question WILL come up on the tests. good luck!
Not my interest at all, just needed it for med school requirements. Hes very helpful and wants everyone to pass, and he is really great guy.

Hands down the nicest and the most approachable professor at UTM, I took this course and TA'd it as well. I can tell you that he truly cares for his students. People do bad in this course because they rely on past midterms/exams and hoping to do good, might work for midterm but you need to know ur stuff, if u do that u'll get a 90

Great guy, uses a trolly of toys so often and is really funny in a nerdy way. Very approachable but for some reason, he seemed to not like me, not sure why. Labs can be good but figuring out how to use the equipment was sometimes challenging. Tutorial was awful, it was 2 Asian TAs, each would disagree on something. Smart but boring as hell.

this prof is the SWEETEST guy at utm!!! he is so considerate of his students (although sadly, i cant say the same for most of the students, who dont bother coming to lecture). if you go through his past tests and exams, you're set for this class. he even posts up solutions to them!!! and he's available for help 24/7. best prof at utm

Very helpful, highly recommended, easy to approach and talk to, has excellent method of teaching through visual aids, Final tests are of medium difficulty, Better to attend his lectures for good grasp of the topics.

Not a bad course but he's decided to make the whole thing multiple choice (test/exam). We didn't get any marks for showing our work which you need in physics so almost everyone did bad. Actual course (labs/quizzes/material) is ok, just the test/exam are hard. Take only if you need it.
Greatest Professor alive.  Guaranteed 4.0 GPA if you listen to his lectures and advice.
Best Prof I ever had. Also amazing to work with. The guy gives the best refernce letters everrrr.
Makes Physics Easier but have to study though
Awesome Professor
By No Doubt, the most amazing professor during first year!His tests & exams were fair and he loves helping his students out. AMAZING PROFESSOR. Definately sparked my interest in physics.
He helps students understand the physics concepts, especially in the practicals. He is an excellent professor to have in physics.
Prof ghobie is a real nice man...but don take this course too lightly after readin all the +ve comments....its not as easy as it sounds...gotta study for it...know the text really well
If you can't do well in his class, physics is not for you :p. He is so helpful, and genuinely cares for his students.

he's the best prof. he made everything so easy for me to understand and he uses so many examples & not just written but he actually uses toys & arrows so that u can actually c & understand wat he's talking about. For labs, he attends almost all of them so if u have a problem where u dont understand something he's there 2 ans them & isnt mad
THE BEST

This guy, is the nicest, most warming person to approach whenever you have a Physics problem. Can't go wrong with that. Been a student and teaching assistant under him for 1 year and 2 years, respectively. Great boss, too. Offers pretty grades to most students too ;)
Best professor ever! Other profs should learn from him. He is one of the only profs that cares about his students and helps them do well. Thanks Wagih!
he is the kindest, most helpful, and cheerful prof at utm, and he makes an effort to know his students and help them understand the material. i loooooved his classes
The MOST amazing prof anyone could wish for. Takes the time to get to know the students & their names...which is no easy task when your class has 200 students. I wish he taught EVERYTHING!
such an amazing prof! he is so enthusiastic! if you ask him a question hell will help you understand.  One of the most amazing profs you will ever have!
Most AMAZING prof you may ever have!!
Very helpful professor, always there when u need him for his kind advice.
Wicked, humble professor
Ok guy
Quite possibly the best physics professor in all of UofT. Very friendly and approachable.
nice guy.
he is cool
Tends to read his own notes from the website during lectures. Very nice person, approachable.
some examples he lectures on are too easy...but what a nice guy

He uses Barbie and other toys to demonstrate physical principles - somewhat entertaining. Is terribly nice, heart-warming really. Not always clear but very generous with help.

I'm not a physics person, but I got a great mark in his class.  You've got to work for your marks, but it's possible to do really well.  He's a proff that's on your side (not common in 1st year proffs).  Very nice, very flexible, very cute and entertain'g

i took the course becoz he is hot...=]

Simply amazing! Not only does he know how to make things easier for u, he can really help u out, unlike the other profs in uft!
The nicest and best Prof in the world.  UofT is fortunate to have such a wonderful person in their faculty.  THE GREATEST!
Great person!! always ready to help out&knows u better than youd ever think psbl

he's great!

he is such a nice guy. he postpones tests if enough people ask him. very clear!
